1 (ii) one representative of the Maryland Association of Boards of
2 Education;
3 (iii) one representative of the Maryland State Education Association;
4 (iv) one representative of Maryland Free State PTA;
5 (v) one representative of the Maryland Association of Counties;
6 (vi) one representative of the Maryland Association of School
7 Personnel Administrators;
8 (vii) one representative of the Public School Superintendents
9 Association of Maryland;
10 (viii) one representative of the general public; and
11 (ix) one representative of the Office of the Comptroller.
12 (c) The Governor shall designate the chair of the Task Force.
13 (d) The Office of the Governor shall provide staff for the Task Force.
14 (e) A member of the Task Force:
15 (1) may not receive compensation as a member of the Task Force; but
16 (2) is entitled to reimbursement for expenses under the Standard State
17 Travel Regulations, as provided in the State budget.
18 (f) The Task Force shall:
19 (1) analyze challenges related to the delay in student enrollment counts
20 and its effect on school funding;
21 (2) analyze the connection between growing student populations and the
22 provision of school funding; and
23 (3) make recommendations regarding improvements to the provision of
24 school funding.
25 (g) On or before December 15, 2025, the Task Force shall report its findings and
26 recommendations to the Governor and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State
27 Government Article, the General Assembly.
28 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
29 1, 2025. It shall remain effective for a period of 1 year and, at the end of June 30, 2026, this

